The Labour Party factional leader, Lamidi Apapa has been reportedly caught quarrelling over a seat in an Abuja court on Wednesday. In a viral video, Apapa could be seen fighting over seats reserved by members of the party and saying that he was representing the party and had the right to the seat. Apapa, who has been attempting to take over leadership of the party since the presidential election was concluded, arrived at the Presidential Election Petition Court on Wednesday with other members of his faction.